{
  "text": "Here we establish two results similar to those stated in [CITATION_1] , which we shall use for numerical experiments of the Riemann problem (2.1), (2.11) . The first one is a convergence criterion in Lfoc, for the sequence u(x,t; At/n, Tin) constructed above for the Riemann problem. By this theorem , the convergence of this sequence is associated with the convergence of certain averages along the rays of constant x/t in the (a;, t)-plane, based on u(x, t; At, k). The proof of the theorem is given in the appendix. for any h \u00a3 Ca(R2) along every ray of fixed x/t. Its value at each time step can easily be calculated numerically. In particular, we shall determine in our numerical experiments u(x,t) and F(x,t), the average values of the state variable and the flux function, which approximate the expectation values of these state functions with respect to the m-v solution, generated from un(x,t).",
